name: Air Fryer Oven Brownies
author: Yoly
summary: I made this recipe in my Cuisinart® Air Fryer Oven and my brownies wound up with a crispy and crackly top yet soft and gooey in the center. Air frying the brownies cuts the baking time in half and there's no need to preheat your air fryer oven!
ingredients: 2 (1 ounce) squares unsweetened baking chocolate, melted
1 teaspoon powdered sugar, or to taste  (Optional)
directions: Grease and flour an 8x8-inch square pan
Sift flour, baking powder, and salt together in a bowl
Beat sugar and butter together in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy
Beat in eggs until a smooth batter forms
Beat in chocolate and vanilla extract
Stir in the flour mixture until just incorporated; fold in walnuts
Spread batter into the prepared square pan
Place pan in the air fryer basket
Place on the lowest rack in air fryer oven and cook at 300 degrees F (150 degrees C) until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 18 to 25 minutes
Cool completely in the pan, about 30 minutes
Cut into 9 squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar
